          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>What's the difference between professional and DIY house painting?</h3>
            <p>Professional house painters use premium materials, proper preparation techniques, and years of experience to ensure lasting results. DIY projects often skip crucial steps like surface prep and use lower-quality materials, leading to shorter lifespans and potential problems.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Do you provide color consultation services?</h3>
            <p>Yes! We offer basic color guidance at no charge and full color consultation services. Our experience helps you choose colors that work with your home's architecture, lighting, and personal style.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>What paint brands do you use?</h3>
            <p>We use professional-grade paints from Sherwin-Williams, Benjamin Moore, and PPG. These brands offer superior coverage, durability, and color retention compared to retail options.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>How do you protect my furniture and belongings?</h3>
            <p>We use professional-grade plastic sheeting, drop cloths, and masking tape to protect all surfaces. We move light furniture as needed and ensure complete protection of your valuable items.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Can you match existing paint colors?</h3>
            <p>Yes, we can match most existing paint colors using professional color-matching tools. This is especially useful for touch-ups and additions to your home.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Do you offer warranties on your work?</h3>
            <p>Yes, we provide workmanship warranties on our labor and standard manufacturer warranties on materials. Specific warranty terms are outlined in your project proposal.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>What happens if it rains during exterior painting?</h3>
            <p>We monitor weather closely and adjust our schedule accordingly. If rain or high humidity would compromise quality, we pause work and resume at the first safe opportunity.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Do you handle lead paint safely?</h3>
            <p>For homes built before 1978, we follow lead-safe work practices and containment procedures. We discuss lead paint considerations during your estimate if applicable.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Can you paint different types of surfaces?</h3>
            <p>Yes, we paint wood siding, brick, stucco, metal, drywall, and more. Each surface requires specific preparation and paint types, which we handle with appropriate techniques and materials.</p>
          </div>
